#: src/sphinx.md:1
msgid "Sphinx Documentation Integration"
msgstr ""

#: src/sphinx.md:3
msgid ""
"Sphinx is a popular documentation generator in Python community. It's "
"commonly used together with services like [Read The Docs](https://"
"readthedocs.org/) which automates documentation building, versioning, and "
"hosting for you."
msgstr ""

#: src/sphinx.md:7
msgid ""
"Usually in a pure Python project setting up Sphinx is easy, just follow the "
"[quick start](https://www.sphinx-doc.org/en/master/usage/quickstart.html) of "
"Sphinx documentation is enough. But it can get complicated when Rust based "
"Python extension modules are involved."
msgstr ""

#: src/sphinx.md:12
msgid ""
"With maturin, first you need to make sure you have added a `pyproject.toml` "
"and properly configured it to build source distributions, for example a "
"minimal configuration below:"
msgstr ""

#: src/sphinx.md:15
msgid ""
"```toml\n"
"[build-system]\n"
"requires = [\"maturin>=1.0,<2.0\"]\n"
"build-backend = \"maturin\"\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: src/sphinx.md:21
msgid ""
"With this `pip install .` should work when invoked in the project directory."
msgstr ""

#: src/sphinx.md:23
msgid "Read The Docs Integration"
msgstr ""

