#: src/sphinx.md:69
msgid "Netlify Integration"
msgstr ""

#: src/sphinx.md:71
msgid ""
"[Netlify](https://www.netlify.com/) is another popular automated site "
"hosting service that can be used with Sphinx and other documentation tools."
msgstr ""

#: src/sphinx.md:74
msgid ""
"Netlify configuration can be specified in a `.netlify.toml` file. Assuming "
"your Sphinx documentation files are placed in `docs/` directory, a minimal "
"configurationfor maturin based project can be:"
msgstr ""

#: src/sphinx.md:78
msgid ""
"```toml\n"
"[build]\n"
"  base = \"docs\"\n"
"  publish = \"_build/html\"\n"
"  command = \"maturin develop -m ../Cargo.toml && make html\"\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: src/sphinx.md:85
msgid ""
"You also need to add a `rust-toolchain` file at `docs/rust-toolchain` which "
"netlify will use to install the specified Rust toolchain that maturin needs "
"to compile your project."
msgstr ""

#: src/sphinx.md:89
msgid ""
"For Sphinx which is written in Python to run you need to add a `runtime.txt` "
"at `docs/runtime.txt`, its content should be a Python interpreter version "
"for example `3.8`. Then a `requirements.txt` file at `docs/requirements.txt` "
"is needed to install Sphinx and its dependencies, you can generate one by:"
